<LP>
   LOS ANGELES -- Hughes Aircraft Co. said it acquired the
Avicom International unit of Lockheed Corp., Calabasas,
Calif. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Avicom, Pasadena, Calif., is a supplier of audio and video
entertainment and communication systems to the commercial
airline industry. It has about 250 employees.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Hughes, a unit of General Motors Corp., said the
acquisition will allow it to offer aircraft makers and
airlines "complete cabin communications capability, including
data handling, and a total service support network." Hughes
already supplies audio signal distribution systems to the
commercial airline industry.
